# SIFT Environment Variables for Vercel Deployment

# --------------------------
# 1. GitHub OAuth Settings
# --------------------------
# You must paste these values into the "Environment Variables" section in your Vercel Project Settings.
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Note: In your GitHub OAuth App settings, make sure the "Authorization callback URL" 
# is set to: https://<your-vercel-domain>.vercel.app/api/github/callback
# (or http://localhost:3000/api/github/callback for local testing)

# --------------------------
# 2. Database (SQLite via Vercel isn't persistent)
# --------------------------
# If deploying to Vercel, serverless functions are stateless and read-only.
# We have already checked in `backend/sift.db` so the visual engine will load the bundled graph
# completely out-of-the-box! No further DB setup required for read-only viewing.
